FG Set to Get Doses of COVID-19 Vaccines The Presidential Task Force on Covid-19 has said it would be submitting its final Report to President Muhammadu Buhari In the next two weeks. The Chairman of the Presidential Task Force on Covid-19 Mr Boss Mustapha who said this at the National Briefing in Abuja noted that this is not the end of the assignment as the virus has not gone away while adding that there is the significant issue of vaccine to address in the coming months and years. Our correspondent Nathan Williams reports that the Minister of Health, Dr. Osagie Ehanire, disclosed during the Covid-19 briefing that the  Federal Government is making plans to procure at least 20 million vaccines to begin the process of inoculating the populace from the deadly covid-19 disease. The Executive Director and Chief Executive Officer of the National Primary Health Care Development Agency, Dr. Faisal Shuaib also mentioned that the global community led by the World Health Organization ,  The Alliance for Vaccines and Immunization and the Coalition for Epidemic Preparedness Innovations established the Covid-19 facility to assist low and middle income countries like Nigeria to access the vaccines. Meanwhile, PTF National Coordinator, Dr Sani Aliyu has said a committee had been set up to investigate those unscrupulous elements behind the fake Covid-19 test scam unraveled by TheCable, adding that those involved and found culpable will be dealt with according to the law.